Libraries:

library(crosstalk)
library(leaflet)
library(htmltools)
library(DT)
library(sf)
library(here)

Bonus challenge 1

Prepare data and maps

Data

Read and prepare data (same code as provided in 20221206_challenges.R):

# natura2000
natura2000 <- st_read(here::here("data",
                                 "20221206",
                                 "20221206_protected_areas.gpkg"))
## Reading layer `20221206_protected_areas' from data source 
##   `C:\Users\damiano_oldoni\Documents\GitHub\coding-club\data\20221206\20221206_protected_areas.gpkg' 
##   using driver `GPKG'
## Simple feature collection with 38 features and 4 fields
## Geometry type: MULTIPOLYGON
## Dimension:     XY
## Bounding box:  xmin: 2.541481 ymin: 50.68994 xmax: 5.909703 ymax: 51.49938
## Geodetic CRS:  WGS 84
# occurrences giant hogweed
occs_hogweed <- readr::read_tsv(here::here("data",
                                 "20221206",
                                 "20221206_gbif_occs_hogweed.txt"),
                                na = "")
## Rows: 9024 Columns: 9
##  Column specification 
## Delimiter: "\t"
## chr (3): occurrenceStatus, species, datasetKey
## dbl (6): gbifID, speciesKey, decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, coordinateUn...
## 
##  Use `spec()` to retrieve the full column specification for this data.
##  Specify the column types or set `show_col_types = FALSE` to quiet this message.
# transform to sf spatial data.frame
occs_hogweed <- st_as_sf(occs_hogweed,
                         coords = c("decimalLongitude", "decimalLatitude"),
                         crs = 4326)

# count number of "points" in Natura2000 areas
occs_in_areas <- st_contains(natura2000, occs_hogweed)
# get number of points in each polygon as a vector
natura2000$n_occs <- purrr::map_dbl(occs_in_areas, function(x) length(x))

Exercise 1

Create leaflet map:

pal <- colorNumeric(
  palette = "viridis",
  domain = natura2000$n_occs)

leaflet(natura2000) %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addPolygons(popup = ~htmlEscape(NAAM),
              label = ~htmlEscape(n_occs),
              color = ~pal(n_occs)) %>%
  addLegend("bottomright", pal = pal, values = ~n_occs,
            title = "Number of occurrences",
            opacity = 1
  )

Exercise 2

Combine leaflet with data table via crosstalk. Unfortunately, crosstalk doesnt support polygons at the moment (see https://github.com/rstudio/crosstalk/issues/55). Make a leaflet with markers using the centroids of the areas (use st_centroids()):

natura2000_centroids <- st_centroid(natura2000)
## Warning in st_centroid.sf(natura2000): st_centroid assumes attributes are
## constant over geometries of x
shared_natura2000 <- SharedData$new(natura2000_centroids)

leaflet_map <- leaflet(shared_natura2000) %>%
  addTiles() %>%
  addMarkers(popup = ~htmlEscape(NAAM),
             label = ~htmlEscape(n_occs))
data_table <- datatable(
  shared_natura2000, extensions="Scroller", style="bootstrap", class="compact", width="100%",
  options=list(deferRender=TRUE, scrollY=300, scroller=TRUE)
)
bscols(leaflet_map, data_table)

Exercise 3

Add filter slider:

filter_slider(id = "n_occs",
              label = "Number of observations",
              sharedData = shared_natura2000,
              column=~n_occs,
              step=10,
              width = max(natura2000$n_occs))
bscols(leaflet_map, data_table)
